<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="73" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,520,1087]" pageId="2" pageNumber="73">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,276,520,546]" pageId="2" pageNumber="73">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1866" box="[281,510,520,546]" class="Insecta" family="Pyralidae" genus="Locastra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="muscosalis">
<emphasis box="[281,510,520,546]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="73">Locastra muscosalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[524,587,520,547]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–4" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1716,1740]" captionTargetBox="[154,1430,468,1682]" captionTargetId="figure-137@3.[151,1436,453,1692]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–4. Adults. Locastra spp.: 1, L. muscosalis, male; 2, L. viridis, male; 3, L. mizo sp. nov., male; 4, L. crassipennis, male." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911335" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911335/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="73">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
) and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rong &amp; Li" authorityYear="2017" box="[651,751,520,546]" class="Insecta" family="Pyralidae" genus="Locastra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="viridis">
<emphasis box="[651,751,520,546]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="73">L. viridis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[765,831,520,547]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–4" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1716,1740]" captionTargetBox="[154,1430,468,1682]" captionTargetId="figure-137@3.[151,1436,453,1692]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–4. Adults. Locastra spp.: 1, L. muscosalis, male; 2, L. viridis, male; 3, L. mizo sp. nov., male; 4, L. crassipennis, male." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911335" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911335/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="73">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
) are two very similar species, but the former is distinct from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rong &amp; Li" authorityYear="2017" box="[212,312,556,582]" class="Insecta" family="Pyralidae" genus="Locastra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="viridis">
<emphasis box="[212,312,556,582]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="73">L. viridis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the antemedial dark line bent only on vein R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[835,843,575,589]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="73">3</subScript>
and a parallel white line running along with, whereas in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rong &amp; Li" authorityYear="2017" box="[179,280,592,618]" class="Insecta" family="Pyralidae" genus="Locastra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="viridis">
<emphasis box="[179,280,592,618]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="73">L. viridis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the antemedial line is bent on vein R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[695,703,611,625]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="73">3</subScript>
and also on M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[866,874,611,625]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="73">3</subScript>
, and the white parallel line is absent. Furthermore, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1866" box="[151,305,628,654]" class="Insecta" family="Pyralidae" genus="Locastra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="muscosalis">
<emphasis box="[151,305,628,654]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="73">L. muscosalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rong &amp; Li" authorityYear="2017" box="[362,465,628,654]" class="Insecta" family="Pyralidae" genus="Locastra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="viridis">
<emphasis box="[362,465,628,654]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="73">L. viridis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are distinct in the male genitalia: in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1866" box="[883,1037,628,654]" class="Insecta" family="Pyralidae" genus="Locastra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="muscosalis">
<emphasis box="[883,1037,628,654]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="73">L. muscosalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1053,1123,628,655]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–10" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[155,1431,197,1905]" captionTargetId="figure-19@5.[155,1432,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 7–10. Male genitalia. Locastra spp.: 7, L. muscosalis, male; 8, L. viridis, male; 9, L. mizo sp. nov., male; 10, L. crassipennis, male." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911343" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911343/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="73">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
), the uncus is inverted subtrapezoidal, and the juxta is of a concave U-shape at the posterior margin, whereas in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rong &amp; Li" authorityYear="2017" box="[1107,1208,664,690]" class="Insecta" family="Pyralidae" genus="Locastra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="viridis">
<emphasis box="[1107,1208,664,690]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="73">L. viridis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1222,1289,664,691]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–10" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[155,1431,197,1905]" captionTargetId="figure-19@5.[155,1432,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 7–10. Male genitalia. Locastra spp.: 7, L. muscosalis, male; 8, L. viridis, male; 9, L. mizo sp. nov., male; 10, L. crassipennis, male." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6911343" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6911343/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="73">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
) the uncus is sub-rectangular, and the juxta is concave V-shaped on the posterior margin.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
